President Trump has signed into law the VA MISSION Act, a bill that aims to improve healthcare services for veterans. The act will increase veterans' choices and expand access to care. It includes major reforms to the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA), such as modernizing the appeals process, increasing accountability, and expanding GI Bill benefits. The legislation has received bipartisan support and is seen as a significant step forward in providing quality healthcare to veterans. Various members of Congress, state officials, and advocacy organizations have expressed their support for the act and praised President Trump for signing it into law.